{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}

    <!-- header -->
    <div class="header header_thin" style="background-image:url(/images/slider3_mini.jpg)">

        <div class="header_title">
            <strong><span>{{ tour.name }}</span> ({{ tour.duration2 }})</strong>
        </div>

    </div>
    <!--/ header -->

    <!-- breadcrumbs -->
    <div class="middle_row row_white breadcrumbs">
        <div class="container">
            <p><a href="{{ path('homepage') }}">Home</a>  <span class="separator">&rsaquo;</span>
                <span class="current">Tours</span>  <span class="separator">&rsaquo;</span>
                <span class="current">{{ tour.name }}</span></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!--/ breadcrumbs -->

    <!-- middle -->
    <div id="middle" class="cols2 sidebar_left">
        <div class="container clearfix">
            <!-- content -->
            <div class="content">
                <h2>{{ tour.name }} ({{ tour.duration2 }})</h2>
                <!-- content slider: slider_medium -->
                <div class="slider slider_medium">
                    <div class="slider_container clearfix" id="slider4">
                        {% for slide in tour.pictures %}
                            <div class="slider-item"><img src="{{ slide }}" alt="{{ tour.name }}"></div>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider_pagination" id="slider4_pag"></div>
                </div>
                <script>
                    jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
                        $('#slider4').carouFredSel({
                            pagination : "#slider4_pag",
                            infinite: true,
                            auto: true,
                            height: "auto",
                            items: 1,
                            scroll: {
                                fx: "fade",
                                duration: 2000
                            }
                        });
                    });
                </script>
                <!-- content slider: medium_small -->
                <div class="">
                    <div class="post-item">
                        <div class="post-aside clearfix">
                            <div class="entry">
                                {{ tour.overview |raw }}
                            </div>

                            {# buttons #}
                            <a class="btn btn_default" href="{{ path('booking') }}"><span>BOOK TRIP</span></a>
                            <a class="btn btn_blue addthis_button_email" title="Send to a friend"><i class="icon icon-envelope-alt"></i> <span>SEND TO A FRIEND</span></a>
                            {#<a class="btn btn-info" href="{{ path('request_quote',{'slug':slug}) }}">REQUEST A QUOTE</a>#}
                            {% if tour.pdf is defined and tour.pdf is not null %}
                                <a class="btn btn_cyan" href="{{ path('download_pdf',{'slug':tour.pdf}) }}"><span>DOWNLOAD PDF</span></a>
                            {% else %}
                                <a class="btn btn_cyan" href="{{ path('request_quote',{'slug':slug}) }}"><span>REQUEST A QUOTE</span></a>
                            {% endif %}
                            <a class="btn btn_green" href="{{ path('catalog') }}"><span>REQUEST A CATALOG</span></a>

                            <h2 style="color: #B28E1B; margin-top: 20px; ">DETAILED TOUR ITINERARY</h2>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 1 Ulaanbaatar (City tour)</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Arrive in Ulaanbaatar the capital of Mongolia.  Depending on time of arrival and transfer to hotel and after breakfast you will enjoy city tour including: Gandan monastery and visit to the biggest square Sukhbaatar which is located in the center point of Ulaanbaatar. Have lunch in Mongolian Traditional restaurant. After that, visit to Natural History Museum which is famous for its authentic dinosaur skeletons and fossils (Bogd khan palace museum) and visit Zaisan memorial hill to view of whole city from there. Welcome dinner at restaurant and stay overnight in ****hotel. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 2 Ulaanbaatar to Khuvsgul Lake (Murun province)</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>In the morning, fly to the capital of Khuvsgul province Murun. The flight takes one and a half hours. Drive to Khuvsgul national park. Transfer to the camp and lunch. Visit with yak breeding family. Stay overnight in ger at the tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 3 Discover Khuvsgul National park</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>During whole lovely day, you have an opportunity to ride reindeer and observe them. Kayak trip on the lake. Khuvsgul Lake is reckoned among the purest fresh water lakes in the world. Its surroundings right out of a fairytale. Khuvsgul Lake is the second deepest lake in Central Asia and contains 60% as much water as Lake Baikal. Depth of Khuvsgul Lake is 262 meters and 136 kilometers long.  Stay overnight in ger at the tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 4 Khuvsgul Lake (Murun province) to Ulaanbaatar</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Drive to airport after breakfast. Take a flight back to Ulaanbaatar and transfer to hotel.
                                        Dinner at the local restaurant in Ulaanbaatar. Stay overnight in hotel. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 5 Fly to South Gobi, Bayanzag (Flaming Cliffs)</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>After breakfast fly to the South Gobi. The flight takes one and a half hours. Drive to Bayanzag which is located 20 kilometers far from Bulgan soum, where 70 million years ago a lot of Paleontological findings have been discovered. The place is known as Flaming Cliffs so named by Roy Chapman Andrews American explorer who had visited Mongolia in 1922. During two years he searched through the Mongolian Gobi Desert and he found dinosaur fossils and dinosaur eggs about 10-15 cm from the Bayanzag for the first time in the world. Visiting and exploring native land of dinosaurs and taking some photos for beautiful surroundings. Stay overnight in ger at the tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 6 Bayanzag (Flaming Cliffs) to Khongor sand dunes (Singing sand dune)</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Today we will drive to Khongorinn Els sand dunes, the largest sand dunes in Mongolia. These dunes lie in the Gobi Gurvan Saikhan National Park. The drive is through some incredible desert scenery with flat, stony plains; outcrops of vegetation; hills of interesting rock formations; and herds of wild antelope racing across the plains. The roads are flat and fairly even so it will take at least 4 hours. The shifting sand blown by the wind or someone makes sound so it is called Singing Sand Dunes. Stay overnight in ger at tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 7 Khongor sand dunes</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Today we will have a full day exploring the sand dunes and rest after the long drive. The dunes seem to stretch on forever like a soft ribbon of sand draped over the desert. The shifting sand blown by the wind or someone makes sound so it is called Singing Sand Dunes. There is a beautiful green oasis known as Seruun bulag near the Khongor River. Return to the camp for lunch and enjoy feeling silence and a peaceful in the beautiful surroundings Gobi Deserts. Dinner and stay overnight in ger at tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 8 Khongor sand dunes (Singing sand dune) to Yol Canyon</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>We will drive through the National Park until we reach an area of the Altai Mountains known as Eagle Valley. This is approximately a 240km drive on fairly good roads taking about 6 hours. This Valley is nestled deep within the hills and is a haven from the desert heat. Some areas of the valley are continually sheltered from the hot sun and house huge, blocks of ice that gradually melt away during the summer. Very wide at the entrance, it narrows gradually into a remarkable gorge. You have some chance to see wild animals such as ibex and wild sheep, of course to see the vulture. Riding a horse or a camel and trekking to the gorge. Stay overnight in ger at tourist camp. (B, L, D)</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 9 Yol Canyon to Ulaanbaatar</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Drive to airport after breakfast. Take a flight back to Ulaanbaatar and transfer to the hotel and lunch at the finest restaurant in Ulaanbaatar. In the afternoon free time do shopping for cashmere shop, souvenir shop and State Department Store. Enjoy watch national folklore performance by “Tumen Ekh” national song, throat singing, tsam mask dance and so on. A farewell dinner and stay overnight in hotel.</p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sb sb_brown">
                                <div class="box_title">Day 10 Departure</div>
                                <div class="box_content">
                                    <p>Check out from the hotel and transfer to the “Chinggis Khan” International airport for departure. </p>
                                    <div class="clear"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>


                            {# buttons #}
                            <a class="btn btn_default" href="{{ path('booking') }}"><span>BOOK TRIP</span></a>
                            <a class="btn btn_blue addthis_button_email" title="Send to a friend"><i class="icon icon-envelope-alt"></i> <span>SEND TO A FRIEND</span></a>
                            {#<a class="btn btn-info" href="{{ path('request_quote',{'slug':slug}) }}">REQUEST A QUOTE</a>#}
                            {% if tour.pdf is defined and tour.pdf is not null %}
                                <a class="btn btn_cyan" href="{{ path('download_pdf',{'slug':tour.pdf}) }}"><span>DOWNLOAD PDF</span></a>
                            {% else %}
                                <a class="btn btn_cyan" href="{{ path('request_quote',{'slug':slug}) }}"><span>REQUEST A QUOTE</span></a>
                            {% endif %}
                            <a class="btn btn_green" href="{{ path('catalog') }}"><span>REQUEST A CATALOG</span></a>
                            <script type="text/javascript">var addthis_config = {'services' : 'facebook,twitter,email,more', "data_track_addressbar":true};</script>
                            <script type="text/javascript" src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-52b596d25b76435f"></script>

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- sidebar -->
            <div class="sidebar">
                <div class="box">

                    <!-- widget_categories -->
                    <div class="widget-container widget_categories">
                        <h3 class="widget-title">Trip snapshot</h3>
                        <b style="color: #B28E1B">Tour length:</b> <span>{{ tour.duration2 }}</span>
                        <br/>
                        <b style="color: #B28E1B">Available time:</b> <span>{{ tour.availableTime }}</span>
                        <br/>
                        <b style="color: #B28E1B">Region:</b> <span>{{ tour.region }}</span>
                        <br/>
                    </div>
                    <!--/ widget_categories -->

                    <!-- widget_categories -->
                    <div class="widget-container widget_categories">
                        <h3 class="widget-title">Travel map</h3>
                        <a href="{{ tour.mapLarge }}" data-rel="prettyPhoto" title="Travel map" hidefocus="true" rel="prettyPhoto" style="outline: none;"><img src="{{ tour.map }}" width="380" class="frame_box"/></a>
                    </div>
                    <!--/ widget_categories -->

                    <!-- widget_recent_comments -->
                    <div class="widget-container widget_popular">
                        <h3 class="widget-title">Highlights</h3>
                        <ul>
                            {% for highlight in tour.highlights %}
                            <li><a href="javascript:;">{{ highlight }}</a></li>
                            {% endfor %}
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <!--/ widget_recent_comments -->

                    <!-- login widget -->
                    <div class="widget-container widget_login">
                        <h2>Quick inquiry</h2>

                        <form method="post" action="{{ path('inquiry_send', {'slug':slug}) }}" class="loginform">

                            {% for message in app.session.getFlashBag.get('inquiry') %}
                                <mark style="padding: 10px;display: block;"> {{ message }}</mark>
                            {% endfor %}

                            <p><label>Your name</label><br>
                                {{ form_widget(form.name, { 'attr': {'class': 'input'} }) }}</p>
                            <p><label>Your email address</label><br>
                                {{ form_widget(form.email, { 'attr': {'class': 'input'} }) }}</p>
                            <p><label>Your phone number</label><br>
                                {{ form_widget(form.phone, { 'attr': {'class': 'input'} }) }}</p>
                            <p><label>Your message</label><br>
                                {{ form_widget(form.content, { 'attr': {'class': 'input', 'rows': '4'} }) }}</p>

                            {{ form_rest(form) }}
                            <p class="submit">
                                <input type="submit" name="wp-submit" id="wp-submit" class="btn-submit" value="Send" tabindex="100">
                            </p>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                    <!--/ login widget -->

                    <!-- subscribe buttons -->
                    <div class="widget-container subscribe_btn">
                        {#<mark style="padding: 10px;display: block;">OFFER 10% May sale discount</mark>
                        <br/>#}
                        <div>
                            <a href="{{ path('page_show', {'slug':'trip-calendar-2015'}) }}"><img src="/images/group_travel_2014.jpg" alt="Join our group travel 2014"/></a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--/ subscribe buttons -->

                </div>

                <div class="sb sb_dark">
                    <div class="box_title">Included</div>
                    <div class="box_content">
                        <div class="entry">
                            <div class="list_check">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Shared accommodation in ger camp</li>
                                    <li>All meals as listed in itinerary</li>
                                    <li>All entrance fees</li>
                                    <li>Sightseeing as per itinerary</li>
                                    <li>Accommodation in 4 stars hotel in Ulaanbaatar (twin standard room double occupancy)</li>
                                    <li>Transportations by 4WD vehicles</li>
                                    <li>English speaking guide (other language guide on request)</li>
                                    <li>Daily supply of bottled water</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="clear"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="sb sb_dark">
                    <div class="box_title">Not included</div>
                    <div class="box_content">
                        <div class="entry">
                            <div class="list_delete">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>International airfare</li>
                                    <li>Travel insurance</li>
                                    <li>Beverages</li>
                                    <li>Optional activity cost</li>
                                    <li>Excess baggage charge</li>
                                    <li>Single room supplement</li>
                                    <li>Any additional things which are not mentioned above</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="clear"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="sb sb_blue">
                    <div class="box_title">Testimonial</div>
                    <div class="box_content">
                        <div class="slider_quotes" style="margin-top: 45px;">
                            <div class="slider-item">
                                {% if tour.testimonial is defined %}
                                    <div class="quote-text">
                                        {{ tour.testimonial|raw }}
                                    </div>
                                {% else %}
                                    <div class="quote-text">
                                        <strong>Hello Soyoloo</strong><br/><p>Just want to thank you for your wonderful hospitality and expert tour guiding during our trip to Mongolia.  We loved visiting the Husai National Park and exploring the city of Ulaanbaatar.  Our favorite part of the trip was seeing the beautiful countryside and encountering wild horses, camels and eagles.
                                            Thank you so much for showing us around and making sure our trip was a success.  We also enjoyed our driver, Zoloo.  Look forward to planning our next adventure with you.
                                        </p></div>
                                    <div class="quote-author">
                                        <strong>Lisa Berkman, Tour group from USA</strong>
                                    </div>
                                {% endif %}
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="clear"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
            <!--/ sidebar -->
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}